Parliament, Sunday, 19 August 2018 – The Portfolio Committee on Cooperative Government and Traditional Affairs will tomorrow (Monday) conduct public hearings into the Customary Initiation Bill in Limpopo, Jane Furse. The Customary Initiation Bill is intended to provide effective regulation of initiation schools, and make safe the tradition, throughout the country. VENUE: MOSES MABOTA, FETAKGOMO TIME: 09H00 The programme is available here:
	https://tinyurl.com/ya2khv7k ISSUED BY THE PARLIAMENTARY COMMUNICATION SERVICES ON BEHALF OF THE CHAIRPERSON OF THE PORTFOLIO COMMITTEE ON COOPERATIVE GOVERNANCE AND TRADITIONAL AFFAIRS, MR RICHARD MDAKANE. For media enquiries or interviews with the Chairperson, please contact the committee’s Media Officer:
